This paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the integrality ratio of the subtour LP for TSP, which is a linear programming relaxation of the problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Optimization and Control (cs.OC) sub-categories. However, the paper also mentions that the TSP instances are metric and Euclidean, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents a family of TSP instances, which suggests that it could belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions that the integrality ratio converges to a specific value, which suggests that it could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
